<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2187] GString as String[] returns a 1-element array with the whole text</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2187</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is an old bug.&lt;br/&gt;
Case 1)&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; String str= &quot;hello 10&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; str as String[]&lt;br/&gt;
Result: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;h&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;e&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;l&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;l&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;o&amp;quot;, &amp;quot; &amp;quot;, &amp;quot;1&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;0&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is, an array of String with one element per character in the original String.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Case 2)&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; def i= 10&lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; def gstr= &quot;hello $i&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
groovy&amp;gt; gstr as String[]&lt;br/&gt;
Result: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;hello 10&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is, an array of String, with &lt;b&gt;only one&lt;/b&gt; element consisting of the &lt;b&gt;whole&lt;/b&gt; rendered String.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is inconsistent behaviour and may give undesired results when calling methods that expect an array of String&lt;/p&gt;</description>
